ðŸ§  How It Works

This project integrates several Python libraries to enable voice-activated automation:

    Speech Recognition: Uses the speech_recognition library to convert spoken words into text.
    Text-to-Speech: Uses pyttsx3 to convert text back into voice.
    Automation:
        Open Applications: The os library is used to open apps like Notepad and Command Prompt.
        Web & Messaging: The webbrowser module is used to open websites, while pywhatkit sends WhatsApp messages.
        Email: Sends emails via the smtplib module.

Tech Stack

    Python
    Libraries: pyttsx3, speech_recognition, cv2, pywhatkit, wikipedia, requests
